How can I transform a given string in Java to capitalize the first letter of each word, replace a specific word with another, and end the sentence with a question mark, without using any built-in string functions such as capitalize() or replace()?
Here is a sample code to achieve this:
String sentence = "Hello world, how are you doing today?";
StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
boolean capitalizeNext = true;
for (char c : sentence.toCharArray()) {
   if (Character.isWhitespace(c)) {
      capitalizeNext = true;
   } else {
      if (capitalizeNext) {
         sb.append(Character.toUpperCase(c));
         capitalizeNext = false;
      } else {
         sb.append(c);
      }
   }
}
// Replace "world" with "Universe"
String newSentence = sb.toString().replace("world", "Universe");
// Add question mark at the end
if (!newSentence.endsWith("?")) {
   newSentence += "?";
}
System.out.println(newSentence);
